        "## Step 5: Filter Financial Facts to Required Tags\n",
        "\n",
        "The facts.parquet file contains 79,448,144 rows covering 9,641 unique XBRL\n",
        "tags across all filings. Since this analysis only requires six specific\n",
        "tags, the dataset is filtered at read time using a predicate filter, so that\n",
        "only rows matching the required tags are loaded into memory. This avoids\n",
        "loading the full dataset and significantly reduces memory usage."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "XAPZcUroBXXg"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "required_tags = [\n",
        "    \"Assets\",\n",
        "    \"Liabilities\",\n",
        "    \"StockholdersEquity\",\n",
        "    \"NetIncomeLoss\",\n",
        "    \"PropertyPlantAndEquipmentNet\",\n",
        "    \"Revenues\"\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Read only rows matching the required tags using a predicate filter\n",
        "filtered_facts = pd.read_parquet(\n",
        "    os.path.join(\"company_facts_data\", \"facts.parquet\"),\n",
        "    filters=[(\"tag\", \"in\", required_tags)]\n",
