        "## Step 12: Construct Capital Structure Variables\n",
        "\n",
        "This step constructs the five variables required to test Trade-off Theory\n",
        "against Pecking Order Theory, following standard definitions used in\n",
        "empirical capital structure research.\n",
        "\n",
        "Leverage: Total Liabilities divided by Total Assets. This is the dependent\n",
        "variable, representing the proportion of a firm's assets financed by debt.\n",
        "\n",
        "Profitability: Net Income divided by Total Assets. This measures how\n",
        "efficiently a firm generates earnings from its asset base, and is the key\n",
        "variable used to distinguish between the two competing theories.\n",
        "\n",
        "Tangibility: Property, Plant and Equipment (net) divided by Total Assets.\n",
        "This measures the proportion of a firm's assets that are tangible and can\n",
        "serve as collateral, which affects a firm's capacity to borrow.\n",
        "\n",
        "Size: The natural logarithm of Total Assets. This is a standard\n",
        "transformation used to reduce the influence of extreme values and account\n",
        "for the fact that larger firms typically have different capital structure\n",
        "behavior than smaller firms.\n",
        "\n",
        "Revenue Growth: The percentage change in Revenues relative to the prior\n",
        "fiscal year for the same company. Since this requires a prior-year\n",
        "observation for the same company, the panel is first sorted by company and\n",
        "fiscal period end date before this variable is computed.\n",
        "\n",
        "Rows with non-positive Total Assets are excluded before these ratios are\n",
        "computed, since Total Assets forms the denominator for most of these\n",
        "variables and a non-positive value would produce an undefined or\n",
        "meaningless ratio."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "14Sw99MCLf3s"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "# Exclude rows with non-positive or missing Assets, since it is the denominator for most ratios\n",
        "panel = panel[panel[\"Assets\"] > 0].copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Sort by company and fiscal period end date to correctly compute lagged revenue growth\n",
        "panel = panel.sort_values(by=[\"cik\", \"end\"]).reset_index(drop=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Construct core variables\n",
        "panel[\"Leverage\"] = panel[\"Liabilities\"] / panel[\"Assets\"]\n",
        "panel[\"Profitability\"] = panel[\"NetIncomeLoss\"] / panel[\"Assets\"]\n",
        "panel[\"Tangibility\"] = panel[\"PropertyPlantAndEquipmentNet\"] / panel[\"Assets\"]\n",
        "panel[\"Size\"] = np.log(panel[\"Assets\"])\n",
        "\n",
