        "## Step 13: Clean Implausible Values and Handle Outliers\n",
        "\n",
        "The constructed variables contain implausible values that are inconsistent\n",
        "with their economic definitions and must be addressed before analysis.\n",
        "\n",
        "Leverage should logically fall between 0 and slightly above 1, since it\n",
        "represents the proportion of assets financed by debt. Negative values or\n",
        "values far exceeding 1 indicate data errors, such as reporting values in\n",
        "different units within the same filing.\n",
        "\n",
        "Growth contains infinite values, which occur when a company's prior-year\n",
        "revenue was recorded as zero, making the percentage change undefined.\n",
        "\n",
        "To address these issues, the following steps are applied. First, infinite\n",
        "values in Growth are converted to missing, since they cannot be meaningfully\n",
        "interpreted or included in statistical analysis."
      ],
      "metadata": {
